Package com.charliai.activities.register

Class Train

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.ws.rs.core.Application
      • com.charliai.activities.register.Train
  • @Path("/train")
public class Train
extends javax.ws.rs.core.Application
    The Train class provides activity handler support for training data associated with activities, including the storing of training data, updating of training data and interfacing the data with the NLU functions.

    • Method Detail

      • activity

        @Path("/activity")
@POST
@Produces("application/json")
@Consumes("application/json")
public javax.ws.rs.core.Response activity​(java.lang.String data)
        The activity method will handle the receiving and storing of training data associated with the activity handlers. The training data must be in a specific JSON format that is organized into intents, dependencies and synonyms. The data will be validated and stored in the training schema as well as processed to understand intents, entities and dependencies.
        Parameters:
        data - JSONObject with training data
        Returns:
        Response object with status of training
        Throws:
        org.json.JSONException - Exception on processing JSON message

      • nlu

        @Path("/nlu")
@GET
@Produces("application/json")
public javax.ws.rs.core.Response nlu()
        The trainNlu method is a RESTful interface for taking the training data and passing it through the NLU process in order to grain the NLU system. This is a separate method in order to keep the activity training load separate from the NLU training load.
        Returns:
        Response on status of NLU training
